58





5130 Cherry AveSan Jose, CA 95118









I did not expect much of this place, from the reviews. I was pleasantly surprised.

The woman who took my order was helpful. Everything is made to order, and she took the time to explain how I might customize my order to fit my needs. When I asked about alcoholic beverages, she listed them for me and let me know what is most commonly ordered.

It was not immediately clear to me where to go for silverware and soft drinks after we ordered. The store itself is very clean. There are lots of booths and tables, some tucked away in the back for more privacy. 

We ordered the small pad thai and an order of chicken dumplings. I was surprised at the quantity of pad thai offered for an $8 dish. The best part for me was the dumplings, though. They were really good, and the sauce they were served with was perfect. I'm not usually a fan of restaurants that think they know what I will like in a dipping sauce, but this one was good, with just a hint of spice. My husband and I split the noodles and dumplings between us and left satisfied.

I will go back. There are several more noodle dishes I want to try, and I also want some more of those dumplings.







There's better places to eat in this plaza. $20 for pastas that you can make better at home. Got the Penne Rosa with chicken breasts, without the chicken probably wouldn't have finished it. 

Generous portions though.







The pasta was alright. Definitely not coming back. The portion sizes were extremely small. The large looked like it could've been a small. For two large bowls and drinks it was $21 which was not worth it. 

I waited in line a few minutes until the guy in the front finally turned his back around to take our order. 

It wasn't too busy when we got there. There was one customer there and then about four more after we showed up. 

I got the pasta that was featured on the cardboard sign on the counter. It was a little too oily for me.







First time here so thought I'd give it a try since they offered a variety. Had the spicy Korean noodles. It was over-sauced and on the salty side. I poured out the extra sauce and there was still plenty left in the bowl. Couldn't finish even the small bowl because it was too salty. Kids mac and
cheese meal was a good option for my son but I wouldn't come back here. 2 stars for offering variety; otherwise, it would have been 1 star.







My hubby and my daughter superliked in here. We loved trying all their offers and varieties of food. We loved noodles, feeling like we've travelled the world by eating different kind and taste Hahahaha.. Not so authentic but still ok. Hopefully they can offer laksa from malaysia amd singapore the soonest. Thank you for making us full today! Will definitely coming back soon.







Noodles, noodles, & more noodles!

If you and your friends are in the mood for noodles but not sure specifically what type, this is the spot. This was my first time to a Noodles & Company and I really liked the variety. From Penne Rosa (tomato-based cream sauce) to Pad Thai to Steak Stroganoff, there is something on the menu for anyone's taste. 

During my first visit, I tried the Penne Rosa with Parmesan-crusted Chicken Breast per staff recommendation. It was prepared in under 5 minutes. Almost took me longer to go fill my cup up with Root Beer. The food was tasty and filled me up perfectly before returning back to work. 

If I'm in the mood for noodles, but unsure what type initially...I'll stop back at Noodles & Company.







I had Japanese noodle and Korean noodle. The Japanese noodle was tasty, but the only think I don't like was they put too much sauce in Korean noodle, that was why it made the noodle salty. 
 
Overall, good noodle and nice place. Will definitely come back!







My husband and I both had the Japanese Pan Noodles with steak (an extra).   The noodle texture and caramelized sauce were good but the serving contained very little other than noodles (i.e. very few vegetables).     High calorie counts, high sodium, with little nutritional value.







Started being disappointed when we couldn't place an on-line order.  Once we arrived at the location we were overwhelmed at the choices.  We chose a few options and waited for our to go order.  Some of the dishes, Pad Thai and mac n cheese, were just okay.  Our other dishes were pretty good.  The price was good compared to amount of food we got.  They have options for everyone.  We will be going back.







Came in for lunch the other day. I had the penne rosa with a side salad and soup... it was delicious! The place was well managed and clean. The helpful cashier Joseph also let me know they have Noodles rewards! I'll be back for sure! #Points







Their portion has always been inconsistent.  One day my "small Japanese noodle" order can feed 2 adults while another day it was barely enough for a toddler.  There's nothing "authentic-tasting" about any of the dishes since it tastes nothing like the foods from that particular country.  That's like claiming Taco Bell is authentic Mexican food and Panda Express is authentic Chinese food.  Dishes that I've had here:

Japanese noodle - edible
Korean noodle - spicy and that's about all I can say about the dish
Mac & Cheese - offensive
Beef Stroganoff - passable
Chicken Adobo - waste of money

On the bright side, the staff are friendly and helpful.







We are currently addicted to this place!!!! A picture says a thousand words right!? I'll attach one from last nights feast!! 

The meatballs... omg yum!!
Tomato soup is delicious...
Korean spicy noodles are killer!
Burger mac and cheese was so good.... 

Trust us... check this place out!







Decided on this place by doing the ole "eenie meenie mienie moe" method in the new plaza.  We ordered potstickers, spicy Korean noodles and the Japanese pan noodles.  Very tasty.  Definitely coming here again.  Especially since my 12 yr old keeps telling me "oh I like this.  This is good".  Clean, friendly, new, and so he so tasty.  Great job!







I thought I'd try this place since it's new and different.  I looked at the menu and asked the cashier what was popular.  She suggested the top row so I opted for the Japanese Pan Noodles and chose the small bowl.  She asked what meat I wanted with it and immediately offered the steak goes well with it, so I agreed.  I also ordered for my son the kid's meal of spaghetti meatballs with two side options of apples and Kids Crispy, which is a small block of Rice Krispies treat.

When she rang it all up I was surprised that it was about $14, which includes both our meals and a milk.  I thought, ok, not bad as far as price.  So we went to sit down, and as looked at the receipt, I was charged $2.99 for the steak.  You know, it would have been nice to have been told there was an extra charge for the meat since I wasn't aware there was.  

When we received our meals I thought how small the serving was but then I did order a small, right?  And I didn't think there was enough meat to justify the $2.99.

I would have to say my noodles were okay, the flavor was fine but I thought the udon was chewy and it really wasn't that warm.  My son's spaghetti wasn't that warm either but he ate some of it.

Okay, I'll come back and try it again since I did fill out the on-line survey (which I shared in part the same here on Yelp) and received a validation code to redeem, but for what it, it wasn't specified.







Overall a good experience. Everyone enjoyed their dishes and we had several with 6 of us. Most notable was a Small Spicy Penne Rosa /w Parm Chicken ($7.58).

Less notable was the Pad Thai which was good but flavor was quite light in my opinion. Also we had one Small and one Regular ordered and bows were different sizes but content looked very close to same. I will bring a scale when I return to this place to validate their sizes have some significance to justify the $1.40 price difference. 

Also notable was the side of Thai Curry Vegetables $1.50, which was very good /w the Japanese Pan Noodles. I think it would pair a small Pad Thai well and to the overall flavor.







I really don't like to leave poor reviews...

I'm a vegetarian and I'm always so excited when a business offers options such as, "no meat" or even tofu! Today I ordered the Korean noodles with no meat online. When I came to pick up my order a really nice man was bagging my order and noticed there was meat in it, without me saying anything. He apologized, and I watched as he asked the cook to make a fresh one, he even gave me a coupon for a free bowl. I was really impressed with his service. 

When I got home I noticed that the cook did not actually remake the order, they just took most of the beef out. I still had multiple chunks of beef. That was really disappointing. I stayed and waited around while they made me a "fresh" bowl... which wasn't fresh at all. The gentleman that helped me today was awesome, but I hope this can be a teaching moment for the cooks. I'm not sure if I would go back.







I'm sorry I'm in love with noodles and company. I'm from Minnesota and it's a much more popular chain there. I was thrilled when I found out there was a noodles close to me, but then it shut down, I think due to inconsistent experiences at that location. So that was a bummer. I've been to this location twice now with no issues! Yay! And it always hits the spot. I get the penne rosa with feta, a spicy delicious sauce with penne pasta. My boyfriend gets the Wisconsin mac n cheese which is different from most places where they oversaturate everything with too much cheese.







We came here the other day with the family to give it a try, everybody was very happy to find something on the menu that they liked and to give it a try. We placed our orders I was within about 5 to 10 minutes are orders were at our table. Refillable drinks, and very big bowls. They have good stuff on the menu, so it will be hard to choose. The only complaint we have, is finding tables to sit and have an enjoyable meal.







Not much to say besides it was very lackluster. Had the Spicy Korean Noodles and the Japanese Pan Noodles. The spicy Korean noodles had some flavor and a good amount of spice. The Japanese Pan Noodles were flavorless. There were bits of broccoli in the dish but they were pretty much raw and didn't go at all with the cooked noodles.  The highlight of the meal were the Korean meatballs.

Nothing horrible about this place. Just wasn't impressed. Also for the cost I could have made 10 times as much food at home.







Clean place and friendly workers.  Our favorites are the spaghetti meatballs and Japanese pan noodles.  Chicken noodle soup is really good but it says it's seasonal now ...







