        5/25/2017
    

I did not expect much of this place, from the reviews. I was pleasantly surprised.The woman who took my order was helpful. Everything is made to order, and she took the time to explain how I might customize my order to fit my needs. When I asked about alcoholic beverages, she listed them for me and let me know what is most commonly ordered.It was not immediately clear to me where to go for silverware and soft drinks after we ordered. The store itself is very clean. There are lots of booths and tables, some tucked away in the back for more privacy. We ordered the small pad thai and an order of chicken dumplings. I was surprised at the quantity of pad thai offered for an $8 dish. The best part for me was the dumplings, though. They were really good, and the sauce they were served with was perfect. I'm not usually a fan of restaurants that think they know what I will like in a dipping sauce, but this one was good, with just a hint of spice. My husband and I split the noodles and dumplings between us and left satisfied.I will go back. There are several more noodle dishes I want to try, and I also want some more of those dumplings.




