I really don't like to leave poor reviews...I'm a vegetarian and I'm always so excited when a business offers options such as, "no meat" or even tofu! Today I ordered the Korean noodles with no meat online. When I came to pick up my order a really nice man was bagging my order and noticed there was meat in it, without me saying anything. He apologized, and I watched as he asked the cook to make a fresh one, he even gave me a coupon for a free bowl. I was really impressed with his service. When I got home I noticed that the cook did not actually remake the order, they just took most of the beef out. I still had multiple chunks of beef. That was really disappointing. I stayed and waited around while they made me a "fresh" bowl... which wasn't fresh at all. The gentleman that helped me today was awesome, but I hope this can be a teaching moment for the cooks. I'm not sure if I would go back.




